circumstances:
The airplane departed RAF Feltwell on an operation to Brest. While returning to base, it crashed for unknown reasons in Dartmoor, northwest of Ashburton. All six crew members escaped with minor injuries. 
Crew:
Sgt Machin, pilot, 
Sgt Thompson, 
Sgt G. S. Bolshaw, 
Sgt W. F. Bourne, 
Sgt Buckby,
Sgt J. D. Clements.
